cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with dialogue management. It also involves the use of reinforcement learning, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of Deep-Q Networks suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with scalability, which could place it under the sub-category of cs.SD (Software Engineering). Finally, the use of an information sharing mechanism suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
